I think naming is a bit of a mess here. It would be more consistent to spend another object, say `lazyNme` and collect all names in it. Something like:

```
object LazyVals {
  object lazyNme {
    val get = RLazyVals.Names.get.toTermName
    ...
    val flag = "flag".toTermName
    ...
  }
}
```
